<br>
I agree that a 200 mana version of T-Rods would be much easier to swallow.  Verant has made no such claims however, it is only wishful thinking.<br>
<br>
Verant stated exactly the opposite.  A goal of &quot;a net loss over time to counteract the rapid infusion&quot; means their intent is for T-rods to COST us mana to balance the fact it provides instant mana.  A sad side effect is that T-rods become useful for mana transferrence ONLY, just like mod rod 1.<br>
<br>
360 mana gained vs 400 mana spent to cast = a net mana loss of 40 mana per rod.  Sounds a lot like a net loss over time. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uliffthemage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Liff the Mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(10/9/02 9:39:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=74.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   This sucks @$$</span><hr size=1> Why nerf us this hard?  This makes no sense.  <br>
